# parley.nvim Base Layer Manifest
#
# parley.nvim's module declaration for the weave layer compiler. parley is a
# LEAF derivative: it consumes ariadne as its substrate (declared in
# construct/deps as `substrate ../ariadne`) and inherits ariadne's EXPORTED base
# layer through that edge. This manifest declares ONLY parley's OWN internal
# artifacts; parley exports NOTHING downstream (it has no consumers).
#
# Format and verbs are documented in ariadne's construct/base.manifest. The
# leading `internal` token (ariadne#99 composition algebra) marks an artifact
# that stays with parley: it is selected ONLY on parley's own self-walk (when
# parley is the leaf), never leaked into any hypothetical consumer — and,
# conversely, ariadne's own `internal` artifacts (its AGENTS.local.md) never leak
# DOWN into parley's composed AGENTS.md. This is the structural fix for the #95
# bug (the old `symlink AGENTS.md` whose @-import silently resolved to ariadne's
# local file).

# ── Constitution ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# parley's own local extensions. weave concatenates this fragment LAST into
# parley's composed AGENTS.md (after every layer's exported prose — i.e. after
# ariadne's exported AGENTS.base.md / Constitution). Declared `internal` so it is
# parley-only.
internal  prose AGENTS.local.md

# ── Skills ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# parley declares NO `skill` rows. The adapted (superpowers-*) and shared local
# (xx-*) skills are inherited from ariadne via the `skill construct/local` /
# `skill construct/adapted` rows in ARIADNE's manifest (parley's construct/local
# + construct/adapted are symlinks into ariadne, so weave finds them there).
# parley's OWN skills (xx-fix, xx-interview-feedback, xx-pensive, xx-skill-gen,
# xx-voice-apply, xx-voice-gen) are committed REAL directories living directly
# under .claude/skills/ — NOT in a weave-scannable construct/ source dir — so the
# `skill <source-dir>` intent does not model them; weave leaves them in place.

# ── Settings ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# parley declares NO settings row. The settings cascade is driven by the `merge
# .claude/settings.ariadne.json .claude/settings.json` row in ARIADNE's manifest;
# parley's .claude/settings.ariadne.json (symlink to ariadne's base) and its own
# .claude/settings.local.json are the operands that merge consumes.
